The '''Pinkerton Syndrome''' is a derogatory [[Singapore]]an term describing the tendency of some local Asians who tend to consider Caucasians superior, usually having a bias towards favouring Caucasians over locals. 

The term traces its origins from the character of Lieutenant B. F. Pinkerton in the [[Giacomo Puccini|Puccini]]'s opera ''[[Madama Butterfly]].''

